 <section>
    <title>Motivating Activity</title>
<activity>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Let's look at the vector <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> as a vector in <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m>.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move horizontally?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move vertically?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{1\\0}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{0\\1}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How can you write <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> as a linear combination of <m>\colvec{1\\0}</m> and <m>\colvec{0\\1}</m>? 
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move in the <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m> direction?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move in the <m>\colvec{-1\\1}</m> direction?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{-1\\1}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How can you write <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> as a linear combination of <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m> and <m>\colvec{-1\\1}</m>? 
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move in the <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m> direction?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How much does <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> move in the <m>\colvec{1\\0}</m> direction?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Calculate the dot product of <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> with <m>\colvec{1\\0}</m>. How does this relate to your previous answers?
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      How can you write <m>\vec{w}=\colvec{7 \\-2}</m> as a linear combination of <m>\colvec{1\\1}</m> and <m>\colvec{1\\0}</m>? 
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      What is different about the different sets we considered to span <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m> in this activity? Be specific about what aspects will make answering the linear combination question easier to answer.
    </p>
  </task>
</activity>

</section>